casebody.data:
Mindy Jaye ZIED-CAMPBELL, et vir, petitioners,
v.
PENNSYLVANIA, et al. No. 13-6226. Supreme Court of the United States Nov. 12, 2013. Case below, 514 Fed.Appx. 154 .

Motion of petitioners for leave to proceed in forma pauperis denied, and petition for writ of certiorari to the United States Court of Appeals for the Third Circuit dismissed. See Rule 39.8. As petitioner Mindy Jaye Zied-Campbell has repeatedly abused this Court's process, the Clerk is directed not to accept any further petitions in noncriminal matters from Mindy Jaye Zied-Campbell unless the docketing fee required by Rule 38(a) is paid and petition submitted in compliance with Rule 33.1. See Martin v. District of Columbia Court of Appeals, 506 U.S. 1 , 113 S.Ct. 397 , 121 L.Ed.2d 305 (1992) ( per curiam ).
